{{distinguish|G-Power}}

'''G*Power''' is a free-to use software used to calculate [[statistical power]]. The program offers the ability to calculate power for a wide variety of [[statistical tests]] including [[t-tests]], [[F-test]]s, and [[Chi-squared test|chi-square-tests]], among others. Additionally, the user must determine which of the many contexts this test is being used, such as a [[one-way ANOVA]] versus a [[Multivariate analysis of variance|multi-way ANOVA]]. In order to calculate power, the user must know four of five variables: either number of groups, number of observations, [[effect size]], [[significance level]] (α), or power (1-β). G*Power has a built-in tool for determining effect size if it cannot be estimated from prior literature or is not easily calculable.

