{{Spanish name|Manzano|Arjona}}
'''María Gracia Manzano Arjona''' (born 1950){{r|loc}} is a Spanish mathematician specializing in [[mathematical logic]] and [[model theory]].

Manzano earned her Ph.D. in 1977 from the [[University of Barcelona]]. Her dissertation, ''Sistemas generales de la lógica de segundo orden'' [General systems of [[second-order logic]]], was supervised by [[Jesús Mosterín]].{{r|mgp}} She is a professor of logic and the [[philosophy of science]] at the [[University of Salamanca]].{{r|usal}}

She is the author of several books on logic and model theory:
*''Teoría de modelos'' (Alianza, 1990). Translated as ''Model Theory'' ([[Ruy de Queiroz]], trans., Oxford Logic Guides 37, Oxford University Press, 1999){{r|mt}}
*''Extensions of First Order Logic'' (Cambridge Tracts in Theoretical Computer Science 19, Cambridge University Press, 1996){{r|x1l}}
*''Lógica para principiantes'' [Logic for beginners] (in Spanish, with Antonia Huertas, Alianza, 2004)

