{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}} {{Use Indian English|date=May 2018}} '''Vinay Vithal Deodhar''' (3 December 1948 &ndash; 18 January 2015) was a [[Professor Emeritus]] with the Department of Mathematics at the [[Indiana University]] who worked in the area of [[algebraic group]]s and [[representation theory]].<ref name="iu">{{cite web | url=http://www.math.indiana.edu/people/profile.phtml?id=deodhar | title=Profile: Vinay Deodhar | publisher=''[[Indiana University]]'' | accessdate=27 September 2012}}</ref>
==Early life== Deodhar was born in Bombay, India in 1948.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://math.indiana.edu/newsletters/AlumniNewsletter2015.pdf | title=Obituary - Vinay Deodhar | page=9 | work=Indiana University Department of Mathematics Alumni Newsletter | date=August 2015 | accessdate=21 May 2018 }}</ref>
==Career== He earned his Ph.D. from the [[University of Mumbai]] in 1974 for his work ''On Central Extensions of Rational Points of Algebraic Groups'' done under the supervision of [[M. S. Raghunathan]].
He was a visiting scholar at the [[Institute for Advanced Study]] during 1975-77 and 1992-93.<ref name="ias">{{cite web | url=http://www.ias.edu/people/cos/users/vdeodhar01 | title=Community of Scholars Profile: Deodhar, Vinay Vithal | publisher=''[[Institute for Advanced Study]]'' | accessdate=27 September 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.indiana.edu/~asnews/news-release/558.html|title=Professor Vinay Deodhar dies at 66|publisher=indiana.edu|date=5 February 2015}}</ref>
